<br>
Your assumption about most of the high caliber players being in guilds that kill Kunark dragons is probably true right now, but its changing fast.  However, your second assumption -- that those players wouldn't want to go on a pickup run -- is dubious.  Some of the big guilds don't really raid that often, and some of the high level members of those guilds are often scouting around for a pickup raid.<br>
<br>
I suspect that someone could put together a successful pickup raid for one of the Kunark dragons right now, but it would be very hard to assemble all of the right people.  As time goes by, it will get easier.  Once again, for the record I have no intention of trying to put together that sort of raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Pharming PoG would make more sense than pharming VS...<br>
<br>
PoG everything &gt; VS anything<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The drops in PoG are much better than anything that drops off of VS.  However, the drop rates in PoG are low, the respawn times are long, and the faction problems exclude a lot of people.  We will keep going to PoG because a lot of people in our group like it, but frankly I find PoG boring and unchallenging. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udreadwolfff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreadwolfff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/11/01 6:55:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick up slot</span><hr size=1> Adding a pick up slot to the rotation is only going to make it free for all . <br>
